# How does the ‘Referral Scheme’ work?

I am aware that Accessible Surveys operates a ‘Referral Scheme’.  I would like to know how it works and how it can benefit me and any organisations i introduce to Accessible Surveys.

## Why does Accessible Surveys have a ‘Referral Scheme’?

If we are to thrive, we need to let people know we exist.  We have found that our customers are fantastic advocates and frequently introduce us to new organisations.

We want to encourage and reward this.  We have therefore created a paid ‘Referral Scheme’.  This creates benefits for referrers and organisations who are referred to us.

## How does the ‘Referral Scheme’ work?

When you create a customer account on Accessible Surveys, you have access to a ‘Referral’ page as shown in the screenshot below.  



From here you will be able to access and share your unique referral link.



When someone signs up using your link and becomes a paying customer, you both receive rewards (**10% discount** for the referred customer for a period of 12 months, **25% of the total subscription fee paid for the first 12 months for you**).

